dataset.description: Information regarding individuals who are registered to vote. This data can be exported from SURE and can be broken down into various reports for voter, election, and district information. It can be segmented by district, party, political boundaries, address, date of changes, etc.

dataset.title: Voter Turnout
dataset.description: Information regarding individuals who have voted and when. This data can be exported from SURE and can be broken down into various reports for voter, election, and district information. It can be segmented by district, party, political boundaries, address, date of changes, etc.

dataset.title: Annual Disparity Report
dataset.description: Primarily the data from the participation report and EOP report, analyzed and translated into summary statistics

dataset.title: KOZ Program Applications
dataset.description: List of applicants to the State's KOZ program, includes date of application, date of acceptance/rejection, amount of investment, number of jobs reported at the close of the year

dataset.title: Council Districts
dataset.description: Data includes City Council District boundaries, based on 1990 Census population information. Data originated from the Philadelphia City Planning Commission.

dataset.title: Curb Edges
dataset.description: Data includes the edges of drivable pavement or travel-ways for all drivable pavement throughout the city, including traffic flow islands and within parks. Data was originally based on air survey in 1996 and later update in 2006 performed by the Water Department. Streets Department now maintains this data set.

dataset.title: State Senatorial Districts
dataset.description: Data includes polygon boundaries of Pennsylvania Senate Legislative Districts.

dataset.title: US Congressional Districts
dataset.description: Boundaries of United States Congressional legislative boundaries for Pennsylvania.

dataset.title: Green Stormwater Projects
dataset.description: From the metadata: "Green City, Clean Waters is Philadelphia's 25-year plan to protect and enhance our watersheds by managing stormwater with green infrastructure. This feature class represents Green Stormwater Infrastructure (GSI) locations that are currently in the design phase or have been constructed."

dataset.title: Selected Real Estate Development Projects
dataset.description: Contains information about the address, company, square footage, project costs and project status for select developments. This is a record of significant projects related to economic development in Philadelphia.

dataset.title: Contract Data (Professional Services)
dataset.description: The City of Philadelphia, through a joint effort among the Finance Department, Chief Integrity Officer and the Office of Innovation and Technology (OIT), launched a new, online, open data website for City contracts. The site provides data on the CityÆs professional services contracts in a searchable format and includes a breakdown of contract dollars by vendor, department and service type. The site also features a ôfrequently asked questionsö section to help users understand the data available on the site. It also provides the entire data set for download in a Microsoft Excel« compatible CSV format.

dataset.title: Streetscape Projects/Capital Improvement Guidelines & Restrictions
dataset.description: Capital Funding Guidelines, One page program description, Process description and list of recently completed and projects underway

dataset.title: Business Service Manager Activities
dataset.description: Containts information about the address, company, and reason for inquiry.

dataset.title: Business Attraction & Retention Completed Projects
dataset.description: Companies that the Business Attraction and Retention unit has actively worked with to facilitate coming to the City

dataset.title: Lobbyist Activity
dataset.description: Information on lobbying activity by principals, lobbyists, and lobbying firms. The Philadelphia Lobbying Information System is a searchable database of registered lobbyists, principals and lobbying firms as well as lobbying expenses The data was collected to comply with City Code Chapter 20-1200 (and Board Regulation No. 9) and more generally to provide the public insight as to the outside interests who speak with City government officials to influence policy.

dataset.title: Lobbyist Registration
dataset.description: Information on lobbyist, lobbying firms, and principals conducting lobbying in the City. The Philadelphia Lobbying Information System is a searchable database of registered lobbyists, principals and lobbying firms as well as lobbying expenses The data was collected to comply with City Code Chapter 20-1200 (and Board Regulation No. 9) and more generally to provide the public insight as to the outside interests who speak with City government officials to influence policy. Data was submitted to PLIS by lobbyists, lobbying firms, and principals. The intended audience for this data is anyone with an interest in the people lobbying City government. The data collected by PLIS is a public record intended to make the legislative and executive process more transparent by providing the public with a clear picture of all of the outside interests involved in policy discussions.

dataset.title: Elected Committeepeople
dataset.description: This data set is a list of elected Committee People by ward, division, and party. There are some people who resign, pass away, or move away during the 4 year interval.

dataset.title: Qualified Voter Registry
dataset.description: Information regarding individuals who are registered to vote. This data is broken down into various reports for voter, election, and district information.

dataset.title: Real Estate Development Committee Meeting Participants
dataset.description: 5-10 projects a year are presented in front of a committee of PECO, Streets, L&I, the Governor's Action Team, etc. These meetings coordinate department responses to real estate development projects and include discussions of plans and obstacles in development. A full list of Committee Members is available at http://www.phila.gov/commerce/realEstate/developerServices/Pages/DeveloperServicesCommittee.aspx

dataset.title: Impervious Surfaces
dataset.description: Data includes impervious surface features, as would be visible from an aerial perspective. Impervious structures are areas covered by impenetrable materials (i.e. buildings, lots, paved streets/walkways). Data was originally intended for studying and calculating water runoff and drainage and was originally based on an aerial survey conducted in 1996. Data was updated using aerial photography collected between March 25 and April 23, 2004.

dataset.title: City Limits
dataset.description: Data includes the boundary of Philadelphia County (same as City of Philadelphia limits).

dataset.title: State House Districts
dataset.description: Data includes boundaries of Pennsylvania House of Representatives Legislative Districts.

dataset.title: Financial Disclosure Statements
dataset.description: Statements of Financial Interest required either by the Ethics Code, the Mayor's Executive Order, and/or the State Ethics Act.

dataset.title: OEM Deployments
dataset.description: Deployment locations

dataset.title: Flu Shots
dataset.description: Flu shot clinic schedule and locations for the City of Philadelphia. Locations include Philadelphia Department of Public Health District Health Centers, federally qualified health centers and community flu clinics.

dataset.title: Crime - Part I Crime Incidents
dataset.description: From the metadata: "The layer holds Part I crime for the City of Philadelphia beginning January 1, 2006. Part I crime includes, Homicides, Rapes, Robberies, Aggravated Assaults, Thefts. The data displayed is generalized by the crime type and the block location." The data is updated daily. Metadata is included in the zipfile.

dataset.title: Permits
dataset.description: Permit, license, inspection, case and violation data from the Department of Licenses & Inspections. Documentation available at http://phlapi.com/licenseapi.html

dataset.title: Advice/Opinion Archive
dataset.description: Legal Opinions responding to requests for advice.  Can be either Opinions from the Board or Opinions from the Board's General Counsel.

dataset.title: Advisory Alerts
dataset.description: Alerts sent out broadly to the public at large or to specific groups related to specific ethics issues.

dataset.title: Press Releases
dataset.description: Board press releases

dataset.title: Public Hearing Transcripts
dataset.description: Transcripts of public hearings held by the Board as part of the process of creating and amending regulations.

dataset.title: Regulations
dataset.description: Regulations approved by the Board.

dataset.title: Settlement Agreements
dataset.description: Settlement Agreements approved by the Board.
